      <prop type="x-chinese-ref">易經 8 九五</prop>
      <prop type="x-translation-ref">易經 8 九五</prop>
      <tuv xml:lang="zh-Hant">
        <seg>九五，顯比。王用三驅，失前禽，邑人不誡，吉。</seg>
      </tuv>
      <tuv xml:lang="en">
        <seg>The fifth NINE, undivided, affords the most illustrious instance of seeking union and attachment. (We seem to see in it) the king urging his pursuit of the game (only) in three directions, and allowing the escape of all the animals before him, while the people of his towns do not warn one another (to prevent it). There will be good fortune.</seg>
      </tuv>
    </tu>
